<hl>
<seg id=1> Shantou Hi-tech Development Zone Draws Attention of Domestic and Foreign Investors </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Shantou, December 20th. Due to improvement of its investment environment and favorable development potential, Shantou Hi-tech Development Zone has been drawing attention of both domestic and foreign investors. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Certain scientists from Silicon Valley who originally came from Chaozhou have expressed intention to establish hi-tech enterprises in the Zone.  The President of Motorola China and relevant staff from Ericsson have also visited the Zone to discuss investment projects, as well as Taiwan who have shown intention to set up a software development company. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Presently Shantou Hi-tech Development Zone has invested RMB 1.8 billion in the park, having built 370-thousand-square-meters of workhouse, as well as infrastructure such as water, electronics, telecommunication, customs secured warehouse, that have already gone into operation. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Up till the beginning of November, the development zone has seen 177 projects, with total investment capital of RMB 6.4 billion.  About 50% of the projects are foreign invested, and seven of the coming enterprises have been recognized by the state as important high-tech enterprises. </seg>
<seg id=6> This year the zone's accumulated industrial output value was RMB 3.7 billion, output of technical, industrial, trading sectors totaled RMB 4.55 billion, export trade amounted to $127.47 million, and taxes RMB 360 million. </seg>
<seg id=7> At the same time, Shantou has created more than ten regulations and policies to encourage the setting up of high-tech and knowledge-intensive high-value industry. </seg>
</p>
